</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FAFC0AFFD7D08CFADFFA9E17B9" blockId="7.[188,1399,1359,1690]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC0AFFD7D08CFADFFECC1449" box="[189,260,1359,1385]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">HEAD</collectionCode>
. From above 1.9 times as wide as long, 1.15 times as wide as mesosoma; occiput rounded, behind eyes partially finely coriaceous, partially smooth, behind ocellar area with distinct oblique striation over whole length, medial striae almost longitudinal. Vertex smooth and laterally with traces of reticulation. Frons smooth, with a longitudinal midline from anterior ocellus, halfway to antennal insertions this impression fans out in numerous striae, this striate area becomes slightly wider than width of antennal insertions, merging with longitudinal reticulation on malar space. Eyes bare. OOL:POL:LOL = 2.5:8.0:3.0. Head in frontal view 1.3 times as wide as high. Antenna with A1 0.8 times as long as height of head, as long as distance between inner orbits. Length:width of A1–A10 = 14.0:2.0; 4.0:1.7; 1.1:1.2; 2.2:1.5; 2.4:1.8; 2.2:1.7; 2.8:1.8; 3.0:2.0; 3.0:2.0; 4.0:1.9. Flagellar pubescence hardly noticeable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FAFC0AFFD7D08CF954FAA016C8" blockId="7.[188,1400,1732,2025]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">MESOSOMA. 1.5 times as long as wide, higher than wide (20:19). Sides of pronotum smooth, with sparse setae, most numerous on anterior part. Mesoscutum with a row of setae along inner margins of notauli, and along outer and posterior margins of lateral lobes, otherwise bare; disc smooth except for weak rugosity at anterior ends of notauli, these strong and almost complete; mid lobe rather narrowly pointed, covering the extreme base of scutellum; scuto-scutellar grooves narrowly triangular, each of their front margins with six short setae. Mesopleuron smooth. Scutellum with very few setae, smooth, evenly convex. Metapleuron smooth, with very sparse pilosity except for a short white fringe along hind margin. Propodeal carinae short, parallel, dark; area between them smooth, distinctly wider than long.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5D6672FC05FFD8D08CF8F4FEE816C9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4770532" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4770532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4770532/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" startId="8.[189,232,1892,1918]" targetBox="[197,1389,265,1855]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="8B9D36FAFC05FFD8D08CF8F4FEE816C9" blockId="8.[189,1399,1892,2025]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC05FFD8D08CF8F4FEC6165E" bold="true" box="[189,270,1892,1918]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C224D79FC05FFD8D128F8F5FD39165F" authority="Buhl &amp; Asadi" authorityName="Buhl &amp; Asadi" authorityYear="2021" box="[281,753,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotfalizadehi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC05FFD8D128F8F5FDF6165F" box="[281,574,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Platygaster lotfalizadehi</emphasis>
Buhl &amp; Asadi
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2655793FC05FFD8D2CDF8F5FC95165F" box="[764,861,1893,1919]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♀; A = holotype (HMIM); B–F = paratype (HMIM). 
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC05FFD8D103F818FE8F1682" bold="true" box="[306,327,1928,1954]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">A</emphasis>
. Habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC05FFD8D245F818FD4E1682" bold="true" box="[628,646,1928,1954]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">B</emphasis>
. Antenna. 
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC05FFD8D336F818FCD41682" bold="true" box="[775,796,1928,1954]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">C</emphasis>
. Head in frontal view. 
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC05FFD8D400F818FB8D1682" bold="true" box="[1073,1093,1928,1954]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">D</emphasis>
. Head and mesonotum in dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC05FFD8D165F83BFEAF16E5" bold="true" box="[340,359,1963,1989]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">E</emphasis>
. Metasoma in dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC05FFD8D29FF83BFD0816E5" bold="true" box="[686,704,1963,1989]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">F</emphasis>
. Habitus in lateral view. Scale bars: A, F =200 µm; B–E = 100 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FAFC04FFD9D08CFE99FC191055" blockId="9.[189,1399,265,374]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D08CFE99FEDA1003" box="[189,274,265,291]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">WINGS</collectionCode>
. Fore wing 0.75 times as long as entire body, 2.45 times as long as wide, reaching about apex of metasoma, clear, with dense, fine and pale microtrichia; marginal cilia very short. Hind wing 5.1 times as long as wide, with two hamuli; marginal cilia 0.2 width of wing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FAFC04FFD9D08CFE33FB6A13AA" blockId="9.[188,1399,419,651]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">
METASOMA. About 1.1 times as long as rest of body, 2.1 times as long as wide, as wide as mesosoma. Length:width of 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D1B5FE5CFE5F10C6" box="[388,407,460,486]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
1– 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D183FE5CFE0D10C6" box="[434,453,460,486]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
6 = 5.0:10.0; 18.0:19.0; 4.0:18.0; 4.0:14.0; 5.0:10.0; 5.0:5.5. 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D4ADFE5CFB7A10C6" box="[1180,1202,460,486]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
1 with two strong longitudinal carinae, smooth between them. 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D2EBFE65FD24132F" box="[730,748,501,527]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
2 with two smooth basal foveae reaching 0.4 lengths of tergite, between them with a couple of carinae reaching one-sixth length of tergite, this otherwise smooth. 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D111FDD7FEFB1341" box="[288,307,583,609]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
3– 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D161FDD7FEAB1341" box="[336,355,583,609]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
6 smooth, with a few inconspicuous setae in shallow punctures (only about four on 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D517FDD7FAF21341" box="[1318,1338,583,609]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
4, six on each of 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D10CFDE0FE9813AB" box="[317,336,624,651]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
5– 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D15EFDE0FE4A13AB" box="[367,386,624,651]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
6), 
<collectionCode id="ED33AE3FFC04FFD9D194FDE0FE7013AA" box="[421,440,624,650]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">T</collectionCode>
6 finely pointed. Sternite 2 anteriorly flat, without prolongation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3386571FC04FFD9D08CFD28FDAE12D3" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9D36FAFC04FFD9D08CFD28FEE713F2" blockId="9.[189,303,696,722]" box="[189,303,696,722]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">
<heading id="D0D58196FC04FFD9D08CFD28FEE713F2" bold="true" box="[189,303,696,722]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC04FFD9D08CFD28FEE713F2" bold="true" box="[189,303,696,722]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FAFC04FFD9D08CFD7DFBC31279" blockId="9.[187,1398,748,858]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">
In general, body shape much as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D79FC04FFD9D274FD7DFCF41227" authority="Buhl, 1999" authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="1999" box="[581,828,748,775]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iberica">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC04FFD9D274FD7DFD7B1226" box="[581,691,748,774]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">P. iberica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B0BFC04FFD9D28AFD7CFCF41227" author="Buhl" box="[699,828,748,775]" firstAuthor="Buhl" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" pagination="17 - 52" refId="ref9307" refString="Buhl P. N. 1999. A synopsis of the Platygastridae of Fennoscandia and Denmark (Hymenoptera, Platygastroidea). Entomofauna, Zeitschrift fur Entomologie 20: 17 - 52." type="journal article" year="1999">Buhl, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(though this has metasoma somewhat longer) but occiput of 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D79FC04FFD9D10AFC86FE23120F" authority="Asadi-Farfar &amp; Karimpour &amp; Lotfalizadeh &amp; Buhl, 2021" authorityName="Asadi-Farfar &amp; Karimpour &amp; Lotfalizadeh &amp; Buhl" authorityYear="2021" box="[315,491,789,815]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotfalizadehi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC04FFD9D10AFC86FE23120F" box="[315,491,789,815]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">P. lotfalizadehi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2655793FC04FFD9D1C3FC86FD851210" box="[498,589,790,816]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
characteristically striate, in this approaching 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D79FC04FFD9D452FC86FF32127A" authority="Thomson, 1859" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC04FFD9D452FC86FB31120F" box="[1123,1273,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">P. marginata</emphasis>
Thomson, 1859
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D79FC04FFD9D102FCD0FE2B1279" authority="Asadi-Farfar &amp; Karimpour &amp; Lotfalizadeh &amp; Buhl, 2021" authorityName="Asadi-Farfar &amp; Karimpour &amp; Lotfalizadeh &amp; Buhl" authorityYear="2021" box="[307,483,831,857]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotfalizadehi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC04FFD9D102FCD0FE2B1279" box="[307,483,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">P. lotfalizadehi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2655793FC04FFD9D1DBFCAFFD8D1279" box="[490,581,831,857]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with distinctly more slender antennae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FAFC04FFD9D08CFC16FDAE12D3" blockId="9.[189,1398,902,1011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D79FC04FFD9D08CFC16FE2A1280" authority="Asadi-Farfar &amp; Karimpour &amp; Lotfalizadeh &amp; Buhl, 2021" authorityName="Asadi-Farfar &amp; Karimpour &amp; Lotfalizadeh &amp; Buhl" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,482,902,928]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotfalizadehi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC04FFD9D08CFC16FE2A1280" box="[189,482,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">Platygaster lotfalizadehi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2655793FC04FFD9D1DCFC17FD831281" box="[493,587,903,929]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
also has smoother mesoscutum and scutellum than 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D79FC04FFD9D4F7FC17FAF21280" authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="1999" box="[1222,1338,902,928]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iberica">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC04FFD9D4F7FC17FAF21280" box="[1222,1338,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">P. iberica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and more setose scuto-scutellar grooves. 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D79FC04FFD9D242FC3FFC5D12E9" authority="Asadi-Farfar &amp; Karimpour &amp; Lotfalizadeh &amp; Buhl, 2021" authorityName="Asadi-Farfar &amp; Karimpour &amp; Lotfalizadeh &amp; Buhl" authorityYear="2021" box="[627,917,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotfalizadehi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC04FFD9D242FC3FFC5D12E9" box="[627,917,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">Platygaster lotfalizadehi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2655793FC04FFD9D3ADFC20FC3012EA" box="[924,1016,944,970]" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
also has smoother mesoscutum, scutellum and T2 than 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D79FC04FFD9D1F8FC49FD9712D2" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1859" box="[457,607,985,1010]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platygaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="B956EAE8FC04FFD9D1F8FC49FD9712D2" box="[457,607,985,1010]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="38">P. marginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
